cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use readme2demo in your work, please cite it as below."
title: "readme2demo: verified tutorials and demo videos from a repo's README"
abstract: >-
  Verified tutorials and demo videos from your README. An AI agent runs it in a
  hardened Docker sandbox and replays it in a fresh container before anything is
  published. It produces a tutorial, step-by-step guide, troubleshooting doc,
  structured HowTo JSON-LD, and a demo video — nothing a clean-room replay in a
  fresh container did not independently execute.
type: software
authors:
  - name: "readme2demo contributors"
    alias: alphacrack
repository-code: "https://github.com/alphacrack/readme2demo"
url: "https://github.com/alphacrack/readme2demo"
license: MIT
version: 0.6.3
date-released: "2026-07-17"
keywords:
